@startuml seq_02_google_sign_in
title Sequence Diagram: UC-02.2 Sign In (Google OAuth)

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Auth Controller" as Controller
participant "Auth Service" as Service
participant "Google OAuth" as Google
participant "User Repository" as Repo
participant "Redis Cache" as Redis

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open Login page
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Click "Login with Google"
Frontend -> Controller: (2.2) GET /api/auth/google/login
Controller --> Frontend: (3.1) Redirect user to Google OAuth page
Frontend -> Google: (3.2) Redirect user
User -> Google: (5.1) Authenticate and grant consent
Google --> Frontend: (6.1) Redirect to callback URL with authorization code
Frontend -> Controller: (7.1) GET /api/auth/google/callback?code=...
Controller -> Service: (8.1) Process Google callback
Service -> Google: (8.2) Exchange authorization code for tokens
Google --> Service: (8.3) Google access token
Service -> Google: (8.4) Fetch Google profile
Google --> Service: (8.5) Profile data (email, name, avatar)
Service -> Repo: (8.6) Find user by Google ID or email
alt User exists
    Repo --> Service: (8.7) Existing user
else User not found
    Service -> Repo: (12.1) Create new user from Google profile
    Repo --> Service: (12.2) New user created
end
Service -> Service: (9.1/13.1) Generate access and refresh tokens
Service -> Redis: (9.2/13.2) Store auth state (refresh token)
Service --> Controller: (10.1/14.1) Tokens and user info
Controller --> Frontend: (10.2/14.2) Redirect to home with tokens
Frontend --> User: (10.3/14.3) Display home page
@enduml
